Package: pi-clock
Version: 2.0.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.9), python3-pil, python3-psutil, python3-gpiozero, python3-apt
Recommends: python3-pip
Maintainer: Aviral Verma <aviralverma@example.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/aviralverma-8877/pi-clock
Description: Nokia 5110 LCD-based system monitor and clock for Raspberry Pi
 A Nokia 5110 LCD-based system monitor and clock for Raspberry Pi with
 interactive button controls. Features include:
  - Real-time clock display (24-hour or 12-hour format)
  - System monitoring (CPU, RAM, disk, temperature)
  - Network status display
  - System management (updates, shutdown, restart)
  - Display controls (backlight, contrast, volume)
 .
 Compatible with Raspberry Pi 3, 4, 5, and Zero models running both
 32-bit (armhf) and 64-bit (arm64) Raspberry Pi OS.
Installed-Size: 232
